<h3 id="eyedropper">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#eyedropper" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Eyedropper <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/com.github.finefindus.eyedropper"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A powerful color picker and formatter.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@finefindus:matrix.org">FineFindus</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I&rsquo;ve released the 0.5.0 version of Eyedropper. The biggest improvements are the ability to change how a color is formatted (for example customize <code>rgb(r, g, b)</code> to <code>Color::rgb(r, g, b)</code>), two new color formats: LMS and Hunter-Lab, and a placeholder page when no color is picked.</p>
<p>Eyedropper can be downloaded from <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/com.github.finefindus.eyedropper">flathub</a>.</p>
</blockquote>


<h1 id="miscellaneous">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#miscellaneous" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Miscellaneous
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@sonnyp:matrix.org">sonnyp</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Romain <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/xdg-desktop-portal-gnome/-/merge_requests/38">fixed an issue in xdg-desktop-portal-gnome</a> where opening a folder would necessarily be in read-only. Which this change ‚Äì the default will be read/write and the user can select ‚Äúread only‚Äù ‚Äì just like for files. As an app developer, it means you&rsquo;ll be able to use the document portal to let users choose save locations.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@ssssam:matrix.org">Sam Thursfield</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-build-meta/-/wikis/openqa/OpenQA-for-GNOME-developers#running-the-openqa-tests">OpenQA tests for GNOME</a> are now set to run against every change to &lsquo;master&rsquo; in the GNOME integration repo <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-build-meta/">gnome-build-meta</a>. Thanks to everyone who helped us get to this point!</p>
</blockquote>


